      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree 682ebf79e6f4f202a7107a102e6d5fddc5fa1e9f\nparent ae024137bda9fe189f4e7ccf26dbaffd44cbbeb6\nauthor PeterWrighten <peterwrighten@gmail.com> 1749155294 +0900\ncommitter PeterWrighten <peterwrighten@gmail.com> 1749155481 +0900\n\nwallet: Allow read-only database access for info and dump commands\n\nFixes #29559\n\nThe bitcoin-wallet info and dump commands previously failed when\nwallet files were write-protected, throwing 'Database opened in\nreadonly mode but read-write permissions are needed' errors.\n\nThis commit adds proper read-only database support by:\n\n- Adding read_only option to DatabaseOptions structure\n- Adding IsReadOnly() method to WalletDatabase interface\n- Modifying SQLiteDatabase to handle read-only mode correctly:\n  * Uses SQLITE_OPEN_READONLY flag when appropriate\n  * Skips write operations (pragma settings, table creation)\n  * Maintains full read capability\n- Updating bitcoin-wallet info and dump commands to use read_only=true\n- Enhancing LoadWallet() to skip write operations in read-only mode\n- Adding read-only support to BerkeleyRODatabase for compatibility\n\nThese changes allow safe inspection of write-protected wallet files\nwithout requiring write permissions, improving security and enabling\nwallet forensics on read-only filesystem mounts.\n\nBoth info and dump commands now work correctly with chmod 444 wallet\nfiles while maintaining full backwards compatibility with normal\nread-write operations.\n",
